The new city councilors from the ČSSD will have to overcome a certain language barrier in order to understand their old-new colleagues from the ODS in the Prague council and the council.
The daily Aktuálně.cz (Aktuálně.cz) has "tested" the members of the new ČSSD council on how they know the notorious slang that has emerged at the town hall in recent years, when Prague was ruled by its current coalition partners.
The coded dictionary introduced by the Prague political elite during the previous era of Mayor Pavel Bém describes some of the most famous figures, situations and cases in the metropolis.
Surprisingly, the new councillors did not understand the familiar terms.
At least that's what they say.
"Who is Voldemort?"
