"Gambia's President Jammi launched a sweeping witch hunt after his aunt's death, allegedly to have been involved in her death and to try to kill the president himself with black magic."
"He called in shamans from nearby Guinea to help, who, accompanied by police, soldiers and the president's personal security, forcibly escorted randomly selected men and women from Gambian villages to the president's farm in Kanilai," Amnesty International said in a report.
