You don't have to be an NHL player to appreciate the sluggish foam.
This “miracle” is simple.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the absorbed heat, or adapts to your warm body.
There is no pressure, you will not roll over at night like after a hard match.
You'll just sleep better.
Lazy foam also acts as a protection against bedsores.
When choosing a mattress size, add the length of the foot to your height, which is about 21 to 34 cm.
Both men and women with a height of around 180 cm need a bed of 210 to 220 cm.
The minimum width for one should be 90 cm for a double bed, a total of 180 cm.
For single beds, for example for singles, a minimum of 120 to 140 cm is recommended.
For comfort and a possible visit.
