It is also a trend in mattresses.
The raw materials from the oil from which polyurethane foams are made are replaced by natural oils, such as from castor and soy.
Soy is used by all well-known manufacturers.
“The bio of mattresses means that the core is made of a material of pure natural origin,” explains Petr Vašíček from Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used in the production of mattress covers, one of the first was aloe vera.
