Prime Minister Zapatero seems to have understood this too, and his two-pronged statement (the reforms promised after meeting with big business last Saturday and announcing new measures yesterday) suggests that, despite criticism of Merkel, the way has opened up to the idea that things need to be put in order.
But the red line that Germany has drawn is there, and it does not seem to want to move it.
And of the options that can be considered, leaving the eurozone full of not very serious countries cannot be ruled out.
